-> 3x3
Like the 2x2 chessboard, this case is not solvable. After placing the first
two queens in an "L" position (similar to that of a knight's move set)
there is nowhere to place the last queen.
 ___________
| ♛ | X | X |    where X represents spots accessible by the first queen,
| X | X | Y |    and Y represents any remaining spots that are accessible
| X | ♛ | Y |    by the second queen.
