-> 5x5
Due to the odd symmetry of the board (and all other oddxodd boards), the
5x5 has many more solutions to the problem. I found two different types, the Q
shape, and the "rows". With the Q shape configuration, the 4 in a square has 2
solutions, and rotating the entire board brings the total to 8. For the "row"
configuration, it can be reflected across the y axis, or rotated by 90 degrees,
bringing the total for that configuration to 8 as well. I found a total of 16,
but there are almost definitely more configurations I didn't find.
